TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {141017=Ian Bagg was born in the little town of Terrace, B.C. Canada. In 1994, he began doing stand up and quickly became a regular at all the major comedy clubs. After a short three years, Ian had made three appearances on NBC’s “The Conan O’Brien Show”. He hosted Ripe TV’s “The Hollywood Burn” and had his own talk show “The Ian Bagg Show”. He’s since added credits like NBC’s “The Tonight Show with Jay Leno”, CBS’s “Late Late Show with Craig Kilborn” and CBS’s “The Craig Ferguson Show”. He was able to be a part of a half hour comedy special, “A Comic’s Climb” from HBO and “Comedy Central Presents Ian Bagg” (leading him to dating Britney Spears for three days). In love with the art of stand up, he was thrilled when The History Channel asked him to be a part of their special, “The History of the Joke”. Al Gore described his comedy as “controlled chaos”, President Reagan on his death bed described it as an “interactive delight”. Nancy agreed. Do not miss your chance to see Ian., 296883=© 1999-2015 Ticketmaster. All rights reserved.}
